Police released surveillance video Tuesday of a north St. Louis triple shooting that left two men dead and another in critical condition.

The shooting occurred on the 4200 block of West Page around 11:55 a.m. Monday. According to the St. Louis Metropolitan Police Department, 31-year-old Samuel Jackson and 21-year-old Jamie Conner were found on Pendleton Avenue suffering from multiple gunshot wounds.
